Defendant Jason Michael Rix in court with attorney Matthew Adrian Lamke.  Defendant Jason Michael Rix in custody.  Ian Franklin Vance-Curzan appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 40 DAYS in the House of Correction with credit for 13 days time served.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS.
Conditions:
*  Serve 10 days in the House of Correction with huber privileges for work and treatment; GOOD TIME MAY BE EARNED;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety;
*  AODA assessment/treatment;
*  Seek/maintain full time employment;
*  Pay a fine of $150.00 including all costs and surcharges or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment.
